<paragraph blockId="21.[809,1420,605,1043]" pageId="21" pageNumber="952">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,972,812,836]" pageId="21" pageNumber="952">Identification.</emphasis>
The lithophytic habit, creeping stem, and narrow leaf blades is distinctive for the species. The infructescence peduncle in 
<taxonomicName box="[1085,1194,880,903]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Homalomena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="21" pageNumber="952" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[1085,1194,880,903]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="952">H. vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unusual in the genus in its erect, not drooping habit (
<bibRefCitation author="Boyce PC" box="[1193,1325,913,937]" pageId="21" pageNumber="952" pagination="793 - 801" refId="ref49064" refString="Boyce PC (1994) New Species of Araceae from Brunei. Kew Bulletin 49: 793 - 801." type="journal article" year="1994">Boyce 1994</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
